   <note type="biography">
      <p>Landowner. Son of Elizabeth Darwin by her first husband Edward Sacheverel Pole. Stepson of Erasmus Darwin. Matriculated at St John’s College, Cambridge, 1787, but did not take a degree; admitted at Lincoln’s Inn, 1790. High sheriff of Derbyshire, 1793–4. In 1807, assumed the additional surname Chandos, by royal licence, in honour of his ancestor Sir John Chandos (d. 1370; <hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi>). Of Radbourne Hall in Derbyshire.</p></note>
